Prague public transport on Wednesday for the first time on a chip
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be entered in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers will enter the metro, trams and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, it can be purchased by about one hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day and 90-day and annual voucher (this will be valid from January 1, 2009) and at the same time have it uploaded to their chip card in the information centers and offices of the Transport Company in the metro stations Museum, Bridge, Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice Station, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Rabylis.
Coupons can be purchased from yesterday also via the Internet on the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
The service was used by more than four hundred customers in the afternoon.
Those who start using the online store can definitely forget about the service windows in the metro stations, where they have had to regularly stand in long queues on paper tickets.
They buy the voucher over the Internet and upload it to one of the thirteen branches of the City Library on the Opencard card.
"In these places, passengers are provided with a desk with trained service that will help those interested in online shopping and will also upload a voucher purchased on their card," said Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, a spokesman for the project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to upload electronic vouchers to Opencard in self-service vending machines, which are installed in several metro vestibules.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, ticket markers remind and passengers may have noticed them in the metro stations Roztyla, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovick<0xC3><0xA1>, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavsk<0xC3><0xA1>.
"There are now five of them in the city, but by the end of the year there should be eighty of them," he added.
The coupon will check the place of the driver of the vending machine
